President Obama held a telephone call with healthcare workers at Texas Presbyterian Hospital in Dallas to thank them for their efforts in dealing with the first cases of Ebola in the United States. He wished a speedy recovery to the two colleagues who were infected and emphasized the importance of learning from the experience in Dallas. The President also discussed the steps taken to strengthen the country's ability to respond to future Ebola cases. He acknowledged the challenging conditions under which healthcare workers operate and praised the Texas Presbyterian staff for their dedication to caring for others.